Defendant Michelle L Bohn in court with attorney Chris Bailey.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Court addresses the PSI and report filed and the parties make corrections on the record.   
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 2 days)
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  4 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions.
*Contact with the co-defendant to be determined by the Agent;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

OTHER: $490.00 BUY MONEY (payable to Waukesha Police Department to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 1 YEAR; FIRST 8 MONTHS to be served as STRAIGHT TIME, REMAINING 4 MONTHS NON-WORKINGHOURS; (defendant remanded into custody and sentence to begin forthwith);

DAY REPORT CENTER: 6 MONTHS consecutive to Condition Time;

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
